  "texts": [
    "14, 37, 49, [53] [54] [55] [56] [57] [58] [59] [60] Most of these studies were conducted using standardized, pre-formulated questions picked from board medical licensing exam question pools (i.e.",
    "United Medical Licensing Exam (USMLE), Ophthalmic Knowledge Assessment Program (OKAP) exam, American",
    "Heart Association (AHA), Chinese National Medical Licensing Examination) 14, 49, 56, 60, written based on university textbooks 59, reproduced from published case reports 54 or retrieved from social media.",
    "57 These studies typically discarded or re-described questions containing photographs, graphs, figures and tables and subsequently posed them to ChatGPT in open-ended or multiple-choice form.",
    "Albeit with some exceptions 49, 54, 60, most of the works available in literature found an overall accuracy around or above 50% in the majority of the experiments -equaling, in some cases, human performance with respect to recall and knowledge -and that LLMs provided insightful explanations to support its answer choices, especially in scenario-based questions."
  ],
